      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Never cut costs that affect service quality or customer relationships. Companies that reduce response times or skip follow-up calls lose 30% more customers during recessions and take 18 months longer to recover.</p>

        <p>Smart efficiency improvements include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Job costing accuracy</strong>: Track actual vs. estimated costs on every job to identify profit leaks</li>
          <li><strong>Preventive maintenance optimization</strong>: Reduce callbacks by 25% with better initial service</li>
          <li><strong>Inventory management</strong>: Reduce carrying costs while maintaining service levels</li>
          <li><strong>Administrative automation</strong>: Reduce office overhead by 15-25% without staff cuts</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

