      <h2 id="cash-flow">Cash Flow Management</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Cash flow management becomes critical during economic uncertainty. Companies with strong cash positions can take advantage of opportunities while competitors struggle with basic operations.</p>

        <p>Essential cash flow strategies:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Accelerate receivables</strong>: Offer 2% discount for payment within 10 days</li>
          <li><strong>Extend payables</strong>: Negotiate 45-60 day terms with suppliers</li>
          <li><strong>Reduce inventory</strong>: Target 45-day inventory turns instead of 90-day</li>
          <li><strong>Maintain credit lines</strong>: Secure financing before you need it</li>
        </ul>

        <p>The optimal cash reserve for HVAC contractors is 3-6 months of fixed expenses. Companies with adequate reserves survive downturns 3x more often than those operating month-to-month.</p>

        <p>Cash flow improvement tactics:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Require deposits on all jobs over $500</strong>: Collect 25-50% upfront</li>
          <li><strong>Offer financing partnerships</strong>: Increase close rates by 40% on larger jobs</li>
          <li><strong>Weekly cash flow forecasting</strong>: Track 13-week rolling forecasts</li>
          <li><strong>Automate collections</strong>: Reduce receivables by 20-30% with systematic follow-up</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <h2 id="customer-retention">Customer Retention Tactics</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Acquiring new customers costs 5x more than retaining existing ones. During recessions, this multiplier increases to 8x as marketing becomes less effective and customers become more price-sensitive.</p>

        <p>High-impact retention strategies:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Proactive communication</strong>: Contact maintenance customers 30 days before service due</li>
          <li><strong>Flexible payment options</strong>: Offer monthly payment plans for larger repairs</li>
          <li><strong>Priority service guarantees</strong>: Maintenance customers get same-day emergency service</li>
          <li><strong>Educational content</strong>: Send seasonal maintenance tips and energy-saving advice</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Customer lifetime value (CLV) becomes even more important during downturns. A typical residential HVAC customer has a 15-year CLV of $3,000-8,000. Losing one customer costs more than reducing prices by 10%.</p>
      </div>

