      <h2 id="pricing-strategies">Smart Pricing During Downturns</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Avoid the temptation to compete primarily on price. Companies that slash prices during recessions typically see 20-30% margin reductions but only 10-15% volume increases, creating a net loss scenario.</p>

        <p>Effective recession pricing strategies:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Value-based packaging</strong>: Bundle services to increase average ticket size</li>
          <li><strong>Flexible payment terms</strong>: 12-month 0% financing increases close rates by 35%</li>
          <li><strong>Maintenance contract incentives</strong>: Discount first year to secure long-term revenue</li>
          <li><strong>Emergency service premiums</strong>: Maintain premium pricing for urgent repairs</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Price testing during downturns reveals surprising customer behavior. Emergency repairs maintain full pricing power because customers have no choice, while discretionary upgrades require creative financing and value demonstration.</p>
      </div>

